Specifically for content I actually followed a specific process. That started, as you must have seen from the sheet form my work folder. I used to have a lot of ideas. I just dumped them on the sheet and accordingly, following the structure, I would:
1. Write the scripts for whatever ideas I can get.
2. Refine with the help of Chargivity.
3. Brainstorm with friends and ask what hooks are punching and what hooks are not punching.
4. Ideate and research which hook will be the best.


After finishing at least 30 scripts, I would just shoot all 30 contents in a span of 3 to 4 days. Maybe that time took me around 5 to 6 days I guess.

After that once the shooting is done, I would hop on with the editing process and would complete the whole edit in the next 5 to 6 days. I guess the shooting time took that time. It was maybe 3 to 4 days and the editing time was like 5 to 6 days or maybe a week also.

After that I had this bank of content and I would schedule the videos accordingly and then, side by side, create and work on new ideas slowly slowly. In this way I had a bank of content that is consistently going on. In the meantime I can just ideate and brainstorm on the content that I would love to work on or maybe can boom afterwards.

This was kind of my process but it actually didn't work. What worked for me best was when I was original and authentic, not even working but a little bit as you can see. Until now nothing has performed for me yet. I was consistent enough but nothing yet performed best for me. But one thing, definitely, that I saw was that the videos where my efforts were minimum did perform the best. The videos where I was actually kind of just ranting and telling raw stories, sharing raw emotions, those videos actually performed better. I got more comments, more saves, more shares.

I guess you can also see it in the analytics: only one video is the outlier, the 11k views one. 
